<h3>What is GeoMakers?</h3>

<p>GeoMakers is an open community that collaborates to envision, invent, implement and improve open source Maker's projects that involve mapping, remote sensing, navigating, and otherwise understanding our world geographically, as it changes (or has changed) over time.  Using inexpensive DIY techniques, we seek to change how people see and interact with our world. <a href="./wiki/about">Read more here</a></p>

<p>By signing up, you will be joining a diverse group of <a href = "./tag/GeoDreamers">GeoDreamers</a>, <a href = "./tag/GeoMakers">GeoMakers</a>, and <a href = "./tag/GeoBoosters">GeoBoosters</a> that together will develop new, enlightening, educational and entertaining tools and capabilities, with an emphasis on:</p>

<ul>
	<li>low cost</li>
	<li>ease of use/low barrier to entry & high public participation</li>
	<li>open data</li>
	<li>creative reuse of consumer technology</li>
	<li>open source and user modifiable designs</li>
	<li>STEM educational opportunities</li>
	<li>tons of fun</li>
</ul>

